    "What we cannot do, however, is to impose regulations that would slow us down in the fight for our collective survival.",
    "This narrative conflates competition strategy with communicative rationality; competition is now seen as the communicatively rational response to the problems that face us.The AI Now Institute has followed the evolving rhetoric of a supposed AI arms race over the course of five years.",
    "As their report states, the competition rhetoric \"crystallize[s] the notion of AI systems (and the companies that produce them) not merely as commercial products but foremost as strategic national assets\" that need preferential treatment in the form of \"greater state support for a specific kind of largescale AI innovation.\"",
    "14 The question of what exactly are we competing over is a question that has no answer in terms of the final state or product.",
    "In this context, what is important is where the development and adoption of a given technology first occurs."
